# Dashboard (React)

Create React App + TypeScript. UI: React Bootstrap + styled-components. State: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query.

## Structure

```
pages/        Route-level views (HomePage, DashboardPage, admin/*)
components/   Reusable UI (common/, subscriptions/, dashboard/, layout/)
constants/    Shared config (e.g. serverNav.ts for dashboard server shell)
store/        Redux slices + RTK Query API modules (store/api/)
types/        Shared interfaces (ISettings, IServer, User, …)
helpers/      Hooks, theme, Discord/Stripe utilities
```

## Server dashboard layout

Server-scoped routes (`/dashboard/:serverId/*`) use a shared shell:

- [`constants/serverNav.ts`](dashboard/src/constants/serverNav.ts) — grouped nav sections, item metadata (path, name, icon, description), and `getServerNavItem()`
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx) — sidebar + page header + outlet wrapper
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx) — page title row with nav icon, premium badge, and mobile menu button
- Desktop: sticky grouped sidebar; mobile: Offcanvas nav from header menu button
- Layout/nav tokens live in [`helpers/theme.ts`](dashboard/src/helpers/theme.ts) (`layout`, `nav`, `layout.padding`, `layout.breakpoints`)

## Site header

[`components/common/Header.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/common/Header.tsx) + [`Header/styles.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/common/Header/styles.tsx) — global navbar with theme-aligned surface, compact logo, pill user menu, and polished mobile collapse nav.

Add or rename server sub-routes in `serverNav.ts` and `routes.tsx` together.

## Content panel

[`components/layout/ContentPanel.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/layout/ContentPanel.tsx) — shared elevated surface (`ContentPanelRoot`) used by global [`Page.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/Page.tsx) and extended by server [`styles.ts`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/styles.ts) for track/settings-specific nested rules.

## Unsaved changes bar

[`UnsavedChangesBar.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/UnsavedChangesBar.tsx) — sticky bottom bar when there are pending edits. Used by [`Settings.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/Settings.tsx) (all server settings pages) and [`TrackPage.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/dashboard/server/TrackPage.tsx). Settings dirty state uses `settings.changed` in the settings slice; no full-page loader on save.

## Settings pages

- [`NotificationSettingsForm.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/NotificationSettingsForm.tsx) — shared form for Kills, Assists, and Deaths pages
- [`SettingHelp.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/SettingHelp.tsx) — modal help (replaces hover tooltips) on General settings and Juicy pages

## Forms

Global `form label.form-label` in [`styles/index.tsx`](dashboard/src/styles/index.tsx) uses the graffiti tab style (background gradient, border, flush with the control below). Switches and checkboxes use `form-check-label` and are unchanged.

## Track page (Notification List)

[`TrackPage.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/dashboard/server/TrackPage.tsx) layout order: alerts → search → tracked list card. Search is the primary action; page title comes from the server shell header, not a duplicate card header.

- Search card uses `#track-search` anchor and responsive stacked input on narrow widths (`ContentPanel` styles).
- Search results use green-accent styling (`entity-list--search`, "Search results" panel); tracked lists use gold-accent styling (`entity-list--tracked`, `tracked-entities-card`).
- When the list is empty, only `TrackEmptyState` is shown (no empty section headers). When partially filled, only non-empty entity sections render.
- Unsaved state uses `UnsavedChangesBar`; adding from search also triggers a save reminder toast.

